sec.p:
The aim of this review is to examine and discuss some of the history of electrochemical CO2 reduction, as well as its more recent advances, to provide the reader with an overview of the field itself. Through this, this review aims to provide a sense of where the field has come from, as well as how it maybe further develop in the future [17, 18, 17–18]. Among the topics discussed within this paper are: the CO2 reaction processes; including initial activation, catalyst design; both past and present, and finally the use of computational methods to improve our fundamental understanding of the CO2 reduction reaction (CO2RR).Table 1
